# Credentials and secrets

For this project, the user authorizes the agent to **view**, **paste into files**, and **save** credentials when useful for the task—including AWS config (e.g. `~/.aws/credentials`, `~/.aws/config`), `.env` and `.env.local`, API keys, and similar. The user accepts responsibility for keeping those files out of git and for rotating any leaked keys.

Do not commit secrets to the remote repository; respect `.gitignore` for env files.
